    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics\/exclusivity-violation"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Overlapping accesses, but operation requires exclusive access (ExclusivityViolation)"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Swift requires exclusive access to a variable in order to modify that variable. An error is reported if a program attempts to access a variable while it is already in the process of being accessed via another name. These issues can often be resolved by making a local copy of a variable before modifying it.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In the following example, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "count",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is accessed for modification by passing it as an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "inout",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " argument to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "modifyTwice",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". This ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "inout",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " access to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "count",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " lasts for the entire duration of the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "modifyTwice",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " function call. The exclusivity violation occurs because the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "modifier",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " closure also accesses ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "count",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " via the name ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$0",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " while the first access is in progress.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "func modifyTwice(_ value: inout Int, by modifier: (inout Int) -> ()) {",
            "  modifier(&value)",
            "  modifier(&value)",
            "}",
            "",
            "func testCount() {",
            "  var count = 1",
            "  modifyTwice(&count) { $0 += count } \/\/ error: overlapping accesses to 'count', but modification requires exclusive access; consider copying to a local variable",
            "  print(count)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This exclusivity violation can be fixed by introducing a local variable to track the value the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "modifier",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " closure should add to its argument.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "func modifyTwice(_ value: inout Int, by modifier: (inout Int) -> ()) {",
            "  modifier(&value)",
            "  modifier(&value)",
            "}",
            "",
            "func testCount() {",
            "  var count = 1",
            "  let incrementBy = count",
            "  modifyTwice(&count) { $0 += incrementBy }",
            "  print(count)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In this updated program, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "count",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$0",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " no longer refer to the same variable, so accessing them at the same time does not violate exclusivity.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Another common source of exclusivity violations occurs when a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "mutating",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " method modifies ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "self",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "extension Array {",
            "    mutating func append(removingFrom other: inout Array<Element>) {",
            "        while !other.isEmpty {",
            "            self.append(other.removeLast())",
            "        }",
            "    }",
            "}",
            "",
            "var numbers = [1, 2, 3]",
            "numbers.append(removingFrom: &numbers) \/\/ error: overlapping accesses to 'x', but modification requires exclusive access; consider copying to a local variable"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "mutating",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " method accesses ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "self",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " for the duration of the method call, so in this example ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "numbers",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " has two conflicting long-lived accesses, one as ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "self",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and one as an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "inout",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " argument to the method. Again, a local variable can be introduced to eliminate the conflict:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "var numbers = [1, 2, 3]",
            "var toAppend = numbers",
            "numbers.append(removingFrom: &toAppend)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Exclusivity checks play an important role in enforcing memory safety and enabling compiler optimizations. See the Swift.org ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/www.swift.org\/blog\/swift-5-exclusivity\/",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to learn more.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
